rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A business that sells, rents and/or leases watercraft.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Boat Dealer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A business that services and/or repairs watercraft.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Boat Maintenance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A business that provides space for boat owners to store their watercraft in dry dock.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Boat Storage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about boats that are no longer in service.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Boat Disposition

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date that the boat was no longer in service.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the reason why the boat is no longer in service, e.g. sunk, scuttled or scrapped.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fate

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the location of the inoperable boat.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Location

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that contains engines that are components of boats.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Boat Engine

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the number of cylinders in the boat engine, i.e. the number of containers for pistons in an internal combustion engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cylinders

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies in cubic centimeters the total volume traversed by pistons inside the cylinders of the engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Displacement
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use the generic property mso:engineering.piston_engine.displacement instead. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:engineering.piston_engine.displacement]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the type of fuel used by the engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fuel

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the company that manufactured the engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Manufacturer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the type of engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Motor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the nuclear powerplant, if any, that makes up the engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nuclear Powerplant

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the power of the boat's engine in kilowatts.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Power

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies in newton meters the torque of the boat's engine, the tendency of the force of the engine to rotate an object about its axis.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Torque
Engine Fuel
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: Use mso:automotive.fuel instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:automotive.fuel]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all ship and boats fates. These are entities like 'scuttled' and 'sunk'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Boat Fate

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all hull configurations. These are the styles of hulls, which are the watertight bodies of ships and boats.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hull Configuration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for kinds of keels, i.e. the structures on boats that protrude from the center of the hull and provide stability to the crafts.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Keel Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all means of propulsion. These are the techniques that a device uses to achieve motion. Entities include 'nuclear power' and 'wind power'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Means of Propulsion

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all boat and ship motors. These are the devices within the vessel that creates motion for the vessel.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Boat Motor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all ship powerplants. These are the nuclear power plants that provide propulsion to a ship.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ship Nuclear Powerplant

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship's nuclear power plant to the company that manufactured the power plant.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Manufacturer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the power of the ship's nuclear power plant in kilowatts.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Power

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that contains standard descriptors for kinds of rudders, i.e. the structures at the ends of boats that are used to steer the crafts through the water.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rudder Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all boats and ships. These are the vessels that carry passengers or freight long distances across water.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ship

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship to its beam, which is the ship's width at its widest point as measured at the ship's nomimal waterline.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Beam

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a ship to the date that the ship was christened.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Christened

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship to a person who performed the act of christening the ship.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Christening Sponsor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship to the date that the contract to build the ship was awarded.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Contract Awarded

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship to the sovereign where the ship is registered.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Country of Registry

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship to the number of crew members usually aboard for trips.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Crew

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship to the date that the ship was delivered by the shipbuilder to the customer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Delivered

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship to its displacement, also called the displacement tonnage. This is the weight of the water that a ship displaces when floating. This term usually only applies to naval vessels.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Displacement

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship to its draught, or draft. This is the vertical distance between the waterline and the bottom of the hull, with the thickness of the hull included.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Draught

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship to information about the engine of the ship.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Engine

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship to its weight in tons.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Gross Tonnage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship to its hull material. This material used to create the hull of the ship.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hull Material

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship to its IMO, International Maritime Organization number, which is the unique identifier for ships and for registered ship owners and management companies.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: IMO/LR identification number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship to the date the ship's keel was laid. Laying down the keel is the initial step in the construction of a ship, and marks the start of a ship's construction.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Keel Laid

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship to the date of its launch. This is the date the ship was transferred to water.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Launched

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship to the length of the ship along the waterline of the ship.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Length at Waterline

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship to its overall length.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Length Overall

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship to the maximum number of persons, both crew and passengers, that are permitted to be on the ship at any given time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Capacity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship to its means of propulsion.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Means of Propulsion

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a ship to the person for whom the ship is named. For example, the ship the USS Ronald Reagan is named for President Ronald Reagan.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Namer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship to the number of passenger cabins on the ship.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Passenger Cabins

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship to its capacity for passengers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Capacity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship to the number of decks on the ship.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Decks

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship to the mso:location.location at which the ship was built.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Place Built

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship to the port where the ship is registered.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Port of Registry

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship to the date the ship was refurbished.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Refurbished Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a ship to information about the period of time that the ship was in active service. Note that this property is multivalued, because a ship may be commissioned more than once.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Service Period

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship to the average speed of the ship under normal conditions, viz. calm weather and average load.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Service Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship to the mso:boats.ship_builder, who is the agent responsible for building the ship.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ship Builder

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship to its mso:boats.ship_class. A ship class is the set of ships of a similar design.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ship Class

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship to agent responsible for its design, an instance of mso:boats.ship_designer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ship Designer
Owners
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type boats.ship_ownership has been deprecated. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:common.ownership_relationship.asset]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship to its generic size. Generic size includes descriptions like 'small' and 'large'
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship to the site where the ship's wreckage can be found, if applicable.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wreckage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all ship builders. These are the agents that build ships.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ship Builder

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a ship builder, either a company or a person, to a ship that they built.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ships Built

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all ship classes. Ship classes are the groupings of ships that share common design.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ship Class

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship class to the distance, in meters, between the surface of the water and the highest point on boats in the ship class. See also the complementary property mso:boats.ship_class.draft_meters.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Air Draft

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:boats.ship_class to the weaponry outfitted on this class of ship.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Armament Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship class to the weight, in kilograms, of the material that provides stability to the boats in the class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ballast

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a ship class design to its beam, which is the ship's width at its widest point as measured at the ship's nominal waterline.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Beam

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a ship class design to its cruise speed, which is the speed that provides the best range for time during a passage.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cruise Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship class design to the date that it was completed by the designer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date Designed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a ship class design to its displacement, which is the weight of the water in tons that a ship displaces when floating.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Displacement

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a ship class design to its draft, which is the vertical distance between the waterline and the bottom of the hull, with the thickness of the hull included.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Draft

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship class design to the number of days that a ship of this design can typically operate without refueling.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Endurance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship class design to information about the engine used in the ship class design.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Engine

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship class to a standard descriptor for the material, e.g. fiberglass, used to construct the hull of boats in the ship class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hull Material

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a boat class to a standard descriptor for the kind of hull provided with boats in the class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hull Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a boat class to a standard descriptor for the kind of keel provided with boats in the class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Keel Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship class design to the length of the ship along the waterline of the ship.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Length at Waterline

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a ship class design to its overall length in meters.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Length Overall

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a ship class design to its maximum speed in knots.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a ship class to a number indicating how many boats in the ship class were constructed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number Built

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a boat class to a standard descriptor for the kind of rudder provided with boats in the class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rudder Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship class to the area, in square meters, of the sails that are provided with boats in the class. Note that this property applies only to sailboats.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sail Area

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship class to the ship builder that constructed the boats in the class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ship Builder

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship class design to the person or company that designed the ship.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Designer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship class design to information about the engine or motor of the ship class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Powerplant
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use boat.ship_class.engine to specify information about propulsion of a ship class. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:boats.ship_class.engine]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship class design to a standard descriptor for the type of ship that the design represents, e.g. oil tanker, destroyer, ice breaker, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ship Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a ship class design to a ship that exemplifies this design.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ships in Class

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ship class design to the number of armaments provided with the design. Note that this property should eventually be redefined so that its expected type is simply decimal.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Armament

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all ship designers. These are the agents that are responsible for designing ships and boats.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ship Designer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a ship designer to a ship that the person or company designed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Boats Designed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a ship designer to a ship class design that the person or company created.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ship Classes Designed
ships_owned
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use common.ownership_relationship.asset and common.ownership_relationship.owner to specify this information. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:common.ownership_relationship.asset]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ship Powerplant
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type is not necessary. The type boats.engine contains properties for all of the relevant information. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:boats.engine]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Engine (if Diesel)
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use boats.ship.engine or boats.ship_class.engine to provide information about the engine in a ship or ship class. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:boats.ship_class.engine]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ship Powerplant System
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type is not necessary. The type boats.engine contains properties for all of the relevant information. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:boats.engine]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: It's not clear what the intended meaning of this property is. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Powerplant
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: This property is not needed if all of the information relevant to the engine of a ship or ship class is stored on boats.engine. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:boats.engine]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all ship types. These are the informal groupings of ships based on different characteristics or usage. This type is a broader classification of boats and ships than mso:boats.ship_class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ship Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a standard descriptor of a type of ships to a ship class design that exemplifies this type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ship Class

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity type representing the collection of all submarines. These are the submersible vehicles that may be manned or unmanned.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Submarine

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A business that specializes in auctioning automobiles, aircraft or watercraft to the public.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Vehicle Auctioneer
Warship Armament
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: There is no need to have this relationship type. The property boats.ship_class.warship_armament can be redefined to relate a ship design class to the number of armaments provided in the class. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type of this property has been deprecated. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type collecting information about the period of time that a particular ship was in active service, e.g. the start and end dates of this period.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Service Period

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property specifying the end date of the service period of a particular ship.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: End Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property specifying the start date of the service period of a particular ship.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Start Date
